This paper deals with message transmission and time synchronization in wireless sensor networks, which are topics related to network infrastructure (NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC). The paper also proposes an optimal approach to reduce message transmissions while maintaining end-to-end delay and synchronization accuracy, which involves optimization and information theory (IT) concepts. Additionally, the paper discusses a novel time synchronization scheme, which falls under the category of systems and control (SY). Finally, the paper uses integer linear programming, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (LG).
